The project doesn't exist on disk yet, so I'll give you the configuration based on the standard stdio transport (the default for C# MCP servers).

Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

**If your server uses HTTP** (i.e., references `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore`), use this instead:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "http://localhost:3001"
    }
  }
}
```

**To verify it works:**
1. Open Copilot Chat → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the **wrench icon** (Select Tools) → confirm your tools are listed
3. If tools don't appear, run `dotnet build` and restart the server
